In the battle of the broadcasters, Sky has announced plans to launch its own mobile network, powered by O2. 

O2's owner Telefónica UK  will give Sky wholesale access to 2G, 3G and 4G voice and data services, with the first deals expecting to launch in 2016.

Sky is hoping to rival fellow broadcaster Virgin Media, which uses EE's network for its mobile services, and BT, which is said to be in talks to buy EE.

